Always read the README file at the root of the directory to see how to use the project. Always read the DOCs directory to understand the project.

When building a feature:
1. Create a new branch for this feature.
2. Understand the architecture first.
3. Only make minimal changes needed.
4. Check for duplicate code paths.
5. Keep things DRY
6. Break down big files
7. Break down big functions
8. Write tests to validate.
9. Make sure all test pass
10. Make sure all linting errors are resolved.
11. Start back at step 3 until it meets all the requirements.
12. Commit the code
13. Push the branch and create a Pull Request.